title: Understanding Data Units
text: Data storage is measured in units that increase in size. The most common units are kilobyte, megabyte, gigabyte, and terabyte.

title: Order of Units
text: The order of these units from smallest to largest is: kilobyte, megabyte, gigabyte, terabyte, and they increase by $$___$$.

title: Comparing Gigabyte and Terabyte
text: A gigabyte is smaller than a terabyte. A terabyte is 1,024 times larger than a gigabyte.
